<subSubSection lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,492,1470,1530]" box="[151,411,1505,1530]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,160,1505,1530]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">(</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[160,258,1505,1529]" captionStart="PLATE 2" captionStartId="23.[151,233,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,199,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-84@23.[151,1436,193,1893]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="PLATE 2. A–H. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Licontinia recurvata, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Licontinia multisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (C) Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Panoldia minuta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Sapingia calcaris, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Stalolidia setacea, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Stalolidia bulbata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Stalolidia flangella, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Plate 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[270,403,1505,1529]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–92" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[212,1367,226,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-66@27.[198,1384,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 85–92. Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov. (85) pygofer, lateral view; (86) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (87) right style, lateral view; (88) right style, dorsal view; (89) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (90) aedeagus, dorsal view; (91) connective, dorsal view; (92) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs. 85–92</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1577,2034]" box="[151,630,1577,1601]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,1577,1601]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 8.00 mm., female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1577,2034]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,458,1613,1637]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Moderately large, slender species. General color dark brown to black and yellow; forewings with clavus black, yellow stripe on each side; scutellum black, basal angeles yellow; pronotum and crown yellow; eyes translucent (
<figureCitation box="[438,540,1685,1709]" captionStart="PLATE 2" captionStartId="23.[151,233,1914,1937]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,199,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-84@23.[151,1436,193,1893]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="PLATE 2. A–H. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Licontinia recurvata, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Licontinia multisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (C) Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Panoldia minuta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Sapingia calcaris, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Stalolidia setacea, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Stalolidia bulbata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Stalolidia flangella, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Plate 2C</figureCitation>
); face yellow with brown longitudinal stripe on lateral margins. Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broader than width of eyes, produced anteriorly about ¼ of entire length, disk flat, lateral margins nearly parallel; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum as long as median length of crown, surface bullated; mesonotum large, nearly twice as long as pronotum; forewings long, broad, 3 anteapical cells present, outer one closed; clypeus long, broad, lateral margins broadly convex, longitudinal carina faint; clypellus about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, apex expanded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1577,2034]" lastBlockId="28.[151,1436,151,392]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,376,1901,1926]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view triangulate, tuft of setae on caudodorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1212,1298,1901,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–92" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[212,1367,226,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-66@27.[198,1384,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 85–92. Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov. (85) pygofer, lateral view; (86) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (87) right style, lateral view; (88) right style, dorsal view; (89) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (90) aedeagus, dorsal view; (91) connective, dorsal view; (92) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate very long, narrow, setaceous in dista1/3 (
<figureCitation box="[698,785,1937,1961]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–92" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[212,1367,226,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-66@27.[198,1384,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 85–92. Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov. (85) pygofer, lateral view; (86) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (87) right style, lateral view; (88) right style, dorsal view; (89) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (90) aedeagus, dorsal view; (91) connective, dorsal view; (92) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
); style very long, about as long as aedeagus, apophysis twisted subapically (
<figureCitation box="[390,477,1973,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–92" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[212,1367,226,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-66@27.[198,1384,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 85–92. Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov. (85) pygofer, lateral view; (86) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (87) right style, lateral view; (88) right style, dorsal view; (89) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (90) aedeagus, dorsal view; (91) connective, dorsal view; (92) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, narrow, tubular throughout, shaft expanded subapically in dorsal view, gonopore medial, exiting lateral in lateral view; (
<figureCitation box="[768,903,2009,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–92" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[212,1367,226,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-66@27.[198,1384,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 85–92. Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov. (85) pygofer, lateral view; (86) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (87) right style, lateral view; (88) right style, dorsal view; (89) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (90) aedeagus, dorsal view; (91) connective, dorsal view; (92) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs. 89, 90</figureCitation>
) connective broadly y-shaped, membrane very narrow between arms, stem short, bulbous apically (
<figureCitation box="[754,840,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–92" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[212,1367,226,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-66@27.[198,1384,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 85–92. Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov. (85) pygofer, lateral view; (86) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (87) right style, lateral view; (88) right style, dorsal view; (89) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (90) aedeagus, dorsal view; (91) connective, dorsal view; (92) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, base broad in dorsal view (92).
</paragraph>
