<figureCitation box="[927,1010,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–92" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1937,1960]" captionTargetBox="[212,1367,226,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-66@27.[198,1384,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 85–92. Panolidia torquesi, sp. nov. (85) pygofer, lateral view; (86) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (87) right style, lateral view; (88) right style, dorsal view; (89) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (90) aedeagus, dorsal view; (91) connective, dorsal view; (92) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
) which will separate it from all other known species in the genus.
</paragraph>
